        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 6:14PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 614 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Drakes Branch, or near Charlotte Court House, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Keysville...
Charlotte Court House...
Drakes Branch...
Mt Laurel...
Saxe...
and Wylliesburg.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for central and
south central Virginia.</instruction>
